ZH: 大烟是一种有害的物质。
EN: Smoking is a harmful substance.

ZH: 我们应该避免吸入大烟。
EN: We should avoid inhaling cigarette smoke.

ZH: 父亲的健康恶化是由于大烟的影响。
EN: Father's deteriorating health is due to exposure to second-hand smoke.

ZH: 每天暴露于大烟中，对身体有很大的伤害。
EN: Being exposed to cigarette smoke every day is greatly damaging to the body.

ZH: 他戒掉了大烟，身体健康也有所改善。
EN: He quit smoking and his health has improved.

ZH: 大烟对儿童的影响尤其严重。
EN: The effects of smoking are particularly severe on children.

ZH: 不管是大烟还是电子烟，对健康的危害都是相似的。
EN: Whether it's cigarette smoke or e-cigarette vapor, the health risks are similar.

ZH: 大烟是导致肺癌的主要因素之一。
EN: Cigarette smoke is one of the leading causes of lung cancer.

ZH: 我非常讨厌大烟的味道。
EN: I really dislike the smell of cigarette smoke.

ZH: 请离这里远点，我不想闻到大烟。
EN: Please stay away from here, I don't want to smell cigarette smoke.

ZH: 大烟对环境也有很大的污染。
EN: Cigarette smoke also causes significant pollution to the environment.

ZH: 不要让大烟接触到婴儿，对他们的影响很大。
EN: Don't let cigarette smoke come into contact with babies, it has a great impact on them.

ZH: 我的朋友决定戒掉大烟，开始过更健康的生活。
EN: My friend decided to quit smoking and start living a healthier life.

ZH: 大烟中的尼古丁非常容易让人上瘾。
EN: The nicotine in cigarettes is highly addictive.

ZH: 为了健康着想，我决定摒弃大烟。
EN: For the sake of my health, I have decided to give up smoking.

ZH: 没有人应该被迫吸入大烟。
EN: No one should be forced to inhale cigarette smoke.

ZH: 大烟的危害不仅局限于吸烟者自身。
EN: The dangers of smoking are not limited to the smokers themselves.

ZH: 禁止在室内吸大烟。
EN: Smoking indoors is prohibited.

ZH: 大烟会加快皮肤老化的速度。
EN: Smoking speeds up the aging process of the skin.

ZH: 长期吸烟会导致大烟纹的出现。
EN: Long-term smoking can cause the appearance of smoker's lines.
